sourcesContent:
import personalHeadshot from '../../assets/images/headshot3.png';
import personalHeadshot2 from '../../assets/images/headshot.png';

import '../ProjectSection.css';

/* For the about me section on the front page */
export const aboutMe = {
    exactClassName: 'home__hero-section home__hero-section-alt aboutmeBg',
    rowClass: 'row home__hero-row hero-alt',
    flexDirection: 'row',
    textWrapper: 'home__hero-text-wrapper home__hero-text-wrapper-alt',
    topLineClass: 'top-line top-line-alt',
    headlineClass: 'heading heading-alt',
    headline: 'Sarah Collins',
    descriptionClass: 'home__hero-subtitle home__hero-subtitle-alt dark',
    description:    
      "Hello! I am a recent Spring 2021 graduate from Embry-Riddle Aeronautical University with a Bachelor's of Science in \
       Software Engineering, seeking an entry-level role within the gaming industry.",
    displayButtonBool: true,
    imgWrapper: 'home__hero-img-wrapper home__hero-img-wrapper-alt',
    imgStart: '',
    heroimg: true,
    img: personalHeadshot,
    imgClass: 'home__hero-img home__hero-img-alt',
    alt: 'Personal Headshot'
  };

  /*For the different sections on the lunar languages page */
  export const aboutLunarLanguages = {
    exactClassName: 'home__hero-section home__hero-section-project darkBg',
    rowClass: 'row home__hero-row project-row',
    flexDirection: 'row project-row',
    textWrapper: 'home__hero-text-wrapper',
    topLineClass: 'top-line',
    topLine: 'Fall 2020 - Spring 2021',
    headlineClass: 'heading dark heading-project',
    headline: 'Lunar Languages',
    lightText: true,
    lightTextDesc: true,
    description:
      'Developed by six students as their senior capstone project, Lunar Languages provides an immersive \
       language-learning experience, allowing users to learn Mandarin Chinese by walking to augmented reality \
      (AR) hotspots located around the Embry-Riddle Aeronautical University Prescott campus.\n\n\
      The project was designed during Fall 2020 and developed during the Spring 2021 semester. The app was released \
      on the Apple App Store and the Google Play Store, though has since been modified by the Embry-Riddle administration \
      outside of the work of the original team.',
    imgStart: '',
    heroimg: true,
    img: 'images/lunarlogo.png',
    alt: 'Lunar Languages Logo'
  };
